    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>While the <strong>userDetails.size</strong> doesn't seemed to be something that a malicious user can control or influence (<em>seeing <strong>UserData.getDetails</strong> would only provide a fix set of items</em>), it is still a good idea to validate the userDetails.size for any potential risk that the size may inadvertently increase to a very large number, causing a Denial of Service.</p>\n<p>So instead of validating the Firstname, it should be the size of the Arraylist that is checked</p>\n<pre><code>static final int MAXSIZE = 2000;\nint arraySize = userDetails.size(); \nif (arraySize &gt; MAXSIZE) { // todo  }\n\nfor(int i=0;arraySize;i&lt;=i++){\n   String rollno=userDetails.get(0)!=null?userDetails.get(0):&quot;&quot;;\n   String subject=userDetails.get(1)!=null?userDetails.get(1):&quot;&quot;;\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
